          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2013-04-24 22:13:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nToro has started the test process",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "44447485f56c302dd55d65267a22ddcc06c2c0a0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-25 00:05:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThere is also commit 8073f0e4b (b=16777), which moves the LDLM hash table over to the lustre_hash, and is probably a better solution to this problem.  It avoids increasing the memory usage on clients (it could actually be reduced), and only increases it as much as needed on the server.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6cd481916062c5fa0ccde4a5f7d85e0cac2a1711",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2013-04-25 08:37:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 5.9/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/5d24a6e2-ad81-11e2-bbea-52540035b04c).  Ran 11 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "9a041af26e22f0dafa7679038ab39ad5f24b20cb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 269,
        "name": "Kit Westneat",
        "email": "kit.westneat@gmail.com",
        "username": "kitwestneat"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-25 15:11:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOleg, I didn't realize it was a server only change, that is good to know. \n\nAndreas, do you mean that it would be better to convert ns_hash to use lustre_hash_t? It looks like it's not referenced all that many times, but would that be a small enough change for b1_8?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7fb7e3f1e2ea334e812c0e99919b3c6a8c5d852f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-26 06:25:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJohann, the question is whether it would be better for b1_8 to change the LDLM hash bucket count to some larger constant value (increasing client memory usage), or change the code to use lustre_hash?\n\nThe patch to move to lustre_hash was landed before 2.0.0, so it has been in use for a long time, though I'm not sure if that code has the SMP scaling fixes that Liang developed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5bc4f7858377892d92f631227863a1af63c15ca7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 7,
        "name": "Johann Lombardi",
        "email": "johann.lombardi@intel.com",
        "username": "johann",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-04-26 07:20:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI would rather bump the LDLM hash bucket count at the price of memory usage, which IMO is still reasonable.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2f5940d6052d36e02b2a0098f3924496a757db40",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 269,
        "name": "Kit Westneat",
        "email": "kit.westneat@gmail.com",
        "username": "kitwestneat"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-26 13:36:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAndreas,\n\nIt looks like the commit you linked to already landed in b1_8 and only affected the export lock list. I think the NS hash was unaffected by the commit. In 2.x, the NS hash uses cfs_hash (commit 864669f7), which doesn't exist in 1.8.x from what I can see, though maybe the semantics are similar to lustre_hash?\n\nWould it be possible to add a test to see if it's running as a server or client, and use an appropriate size? Or maybe a compile time option?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "70c40a9b9dded5db973e913094c484cc0777afb0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 7,
        "name": "Johann Lombardi",
        "email": "johann.lombardi@intel.com",
        "username": "johann",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-04-16 08:44:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2\n\nNo new 1.8 release is planned at this point. Could you please abandon this patch?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
